      "writtenOn": "2017-11-19T21:45:14Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "this test barely tests anything. Please include the full query you expect.\n\nnote that this shouldn\u0027t make this file too verbose if Goconvey is used as meant to: since Prepare is called unconditionally, ExpectPrepare calls can be moved to the containing Convey. Same applies to SELECT:\n\nConvey(\"EnsureDatabase\", t, func() {\n  ... \n  c :\u003d database.With(context.Background(), db)\n  select :\u003d m.ExpectQuery(\"^SELECT id, name, description FROM datacenters$\").\n  rows :\u003d sqlmock.NewRows([]string{\"id\", \"name\", \"description\"})\n  var datacenters []*config.DatacenterConfig{}\n\n  test :\u003d func() {\n    select.WillReturnRows(row)\n    err :\u003d EnsureDatacenters(c, datacenters)\n    So(err, ShouldBeNil)\n  }\n\n  Convey(\"empty\", func() {\n    test()\n  })\n  ...\n  Convey(\"update\", func() {\n    datacenters \u003d append(datacenters ...)\n    rows.AddRow(1, datacenters[0].Name, \"description\"))\n    test()\n  })\n  ...\n})",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 42,
        "startChar": 17,
        "endLine": 42,
        "endChar": 27
      },
      "revId": "860ef1d26b53b0fc03ea43e7c314e347611a626b",
