        "id": 1003211
      },
      "writtenOn": "2017-11-23T00:26:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Hm, apparently sqlite locks very aggressively anytime it does anything. The way datacenters.go is currently structured, you can\u0027t use go-sqlite3 for testing. Right now datacenters.go does something like:\n\ndeleteStmt :\u003d db.Prepare(\"DELETE FROM ...\")\ndefer deleteStmt.Close()\n\nrows :\u003d db.Query(\"SELECT ...\")\ndefer rows.Close()\n\nfor rows.next() {\n  if dc needs to be deleted {\n    deleteStmt.Exec(id)\n  }\n}\n\nWhich results in \"table is locked\" because rows.Close() hasn\u0027t been called yet and we\u0027re trying to execute another statement. I would likely have to restructure to something like:\n\ndcs :\u003d []int\nrows :\u003d db.Query(\"SELECT ...\")\nfor rows.Next() {\n  if dc needs to be deleted {\n    append(dcs, id)\n  }\n}\nrows.Close()\n\ndeleteStmt :\u003d db.Prepare(\"DELETE FROM ...\")\nfor _, id :\u003d range ids {\n  deleteStmt.Exec(id)\n}\n\nI wonder if MySQL has the same issue.",
      "parentUuid": "f53c74bf_dbb818f8",
